  body.docs


    .jumbotron

      h1 Flex Tools
      p Set of flexbox based layout class-helpers for HTML tags.

    
    h1 Initializing
    p #[code f-box] enables flexbox. Outer container works as block.
    p #[code f-align] enables flexbox. Outer container works as inline-block.

    h1 Aligning
    p #[code f-align--Y-X] controls the align element. #[code Y] controls aligning at the vertical axis. #[code X] - controls the horisontal one.

    p #[strong Example]
    .example.example--align
      p #[code f-align--]
        select.example__select
          each val in ['1-1', '1-2', '1-3', '2-1', '2-2', '2-3', '3-1', '3-2', '3-3', '1-13', '2-13', '3-13', '13-1', '13-2', '13-3', '13-13']
            option(value='#{val}')= val

      .example__list.f-box.f-align--1-1
        - i = 0
        while i < 3
          .f-box.f-align--2-2.example__unit This is aligning example
          - i ++


    h1 Grid

    p #[code f-grid--N] - where #[code N] equal of base columns amount

    p Grid controlled by settings values: 
    p #[code $grid-gutter] - gutter between columns
    p #[code $grid-columns] - set column counts

    p By default we have 10px gutter and 12 column. Enjoy!
    p #[strong Example]
    .example.example--grid
      .example__list
        mixin grid(i, max)
          while i < max
            .f-box.f-gap--L
              .f-box.f-align--2-2.f-gutter.example__unit(class='f-grid--'+i) Grid #{i}
              .f-box.f-align--2-2.f-gutter.example__unit(class='f-grid--'+(max - i)) Grid #{max - i}
            - i ++
        +grid(1,12)


    h1 Gap
    p You can control gutters inside flexbox container. You can chose from one of 3 different gaps:
    p Gaps worked with grid or any other columns, even outside from flex container.
    p #[strong Example]
    .example.example--gap
      p #[code f-dir--]
        select.example__select
          each val in ['S', 'M', 'L']
            option(value='#{val}')= val

      .example__list.f-box.f-gap--S
        - i = 1
        while i <= 3
          .f-box.f-grid--4.f-align--2-2.example__unit Column 1/3
          - i++
      .example__list.f-box.f-gap--S
        - i = 1
        while i <= 6
          .f-box.f-grid--2.f-align--2-2.example__unit Column 1/6
          - i++


    h1 Filling
    p #[code f-fill] usefull when you need to fit all available space with some block. 


    h1 Direction
    p #[code f-dir--N] allows you to change direction of children elements inside box.
    p #[strong Example]
      .example.example--dir
        p #[code f-dir--]
          select.example__select
            each val in ['row', 'col', 'row-rvs', 'col-rvs']
              option(value='#{val}')= val

        .example__list.f-box
          - i = 1
          while i <= 3
            .f-box.f-align--2-2.example__unit Box #{i}
            - i ++


    h1 Options
    p #[code f-option--reverse] - change flexbox model from #[code row] to #[code column]
    p #[code f-option--nogap] - disable gaps for current item.


    h1 Limitations 
    p Keep in mind, that Flexbox implementation has lots of caveats and bugs.
    p See full list 
      strong #[a(href='https://github.com/philipwalton/flexbugs') here]

    p Perfect for 
    ul
      li Sketches and prototypes
      li Admin or developer panels
      li Projects on Edge

    p Don't recommend for:
    ul
      li Support for IE 9 and lower
      li If you don't want to handle Flexbox bugs


